18/12/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The EU is giving 2.75m euros to BiH to support forensic activities, according an announcement from the European Commission's Delegation to Sarajevo at the weekend.
The money will be used to buy highly sophisticated forensic equipment and to establish a national DNA database.
The initiative is aimed at backing the work of the BiH State Border Service, the State Investigation and Protection Agency and police structures in the country.
(NTV Hayat, Fena - 17/12/06 - 15/12/06)
